   "source": [
    "## DS2500 Final Project\n",
    "#### Ethan McGeever & Matthew Lam\n",
    "######  Deahan Yu Section 1 \n",
    "\n",
    "Research Question: *“During the 2008 crisis, the 2020 COVID shock, and the 2021-2023 inflation period, which indicators moved first and had the strongest relationship with delinquencies?”*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5d8cc176",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The structure of our analysis is as follows: \n",
    "1) Imports and Aggregation\n",
    "2) Data Transformations & Lag Effects\n",
    "3) EDA -- Summary Statistics and Basic Correlation Analysis\n",
    "4) Advanced Correlation Analysis\n",
    "5) Findings\n",
    "6) Conclusion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1e35b95",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Imports & Aggregation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "27bc0236",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import seaborn as sns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
